.TH "gpiod_export_link" 9 "gpiod_export_link" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gpiod_export_link \- create a sysfs link to an exported GPIO node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gpiod_export_link
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct gpio_desc *desc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device under which to create symlink
.IP "name" 12
name of the symlink
.IP "desc" 12
GPIO to create symlink to, already exported
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set up a symlink from /sys/.../dev/name to /sys/class/gpio/gpioN
node. Caller is responsible for unlinking.

Returns zero on success, else an error.
